append headinfo
    meta(name='ROBOTS', content='INDEX, FOLLOW')
    meta(name='description', content='Reaction-Diffusion simulation using Three.js.')
    meta(name='keywords', content='GPGPU, Reaction, Diffusion, Simulator, Gray, Scott, Three')

    title Reaction-Diffusion Simulator

append head
    style.
        #reaction-diffusion-container {
            max-width: 512px;
            max-height: 512px;
            width: 80vw;
            height: 80vw;
            display: block;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
            margin-top: 3em;
            margin-bottom: 1.5em;
            position: relative;
            
            user-select: none;
            -moz-user-select: none;
            -webkit-user-select: none;
        }

append title
    | Reaction-Diffusion Simulator

append content
    object
        #reaction-diffusion-container
    p(style='text-align:center')
        strong Epilepsy Warning:
        |  Some settings can cause bright flashing.

    section
        h1 Reaction-Diffusion Simulator
        p
            | Made with 
            a(href='http://threejs.org', target='_blank') three.js
            | .
        p
            | This utilizes the 
            a(href='http://mrob.com/pub/comp/xmorphia/') Gray-Scott
            |  model to visualize the reaction and diffusion of two chemicals in in 2D. You can mess with the options in the upper-right.
            br
            a(href='https://github.com/seieibob/Reaction-Diffusion-ThreeJS') See the code on GitHub.
            br
            br
            | Note: This only works on iOS with half the usual precision, so some of these configurations will not behave in the same way as they do on a desktop platform.
    
